Jenkins, Ansible, and Linux are frequently used together in DevOps environments to automate the software delivery pipeline, particularly for continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) on Linux-based systems.
Jenkins serves as the automation server, orchestrating the entire CI/CD process. It can be configured to:
Trigger builds and tests: Automatically initiate these processes upon code changes.
Manage pipelines: Define and execute multi-stage pipelines for building, testing, and deploying applications.
Integrate with various tools: Utilize a wide range of plugins to extend its functionality, including integration with Ansible.
